<body>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >AN 11-year-old boy was killed when a model aeroplane </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >crashed into him at 70mph after its pilot lost control, </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >an inquest </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >was told yesterday.
</Rewrite>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >Adam Kirby, from Watford, </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >was unable to hear warning calls from other members of the </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Phoenix Model Flying Club </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >because of the noise made by another aeroplane that was sitting on the ground, the inquest at </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >St Albans </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >heard.
</New>

<New PAsource="" >The accident happened in March, when Adam's father Alan took him to the club on </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Colney Heath</Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >, Hertfordshire, for the first time.
</New>

<New PAsource="" >A post-mortem examination revealed that Adam died instantly from severe skull fractures and brain injuries.
</New>

<New PAsource="" >The plane, flown by </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Graham Reid, </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >an examiner for the British Model Flying Association, went out of control because another pilot was sharing the same frequency, the inquest was told.
</New>

<New PAsource="" >The club operated a system where fliers would stake a claim to a particular frequency by putting a named and numbered clothes peg on a large board.
</New>

<New PAsource="" >Mr Reid's friend </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Timothy Jenkinson </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >had earlier placed an unmarked peg on the board to claim </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >frequency 67. </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >He took turns with Mr Reid flying their model aircraft.
</New>

<New PAsource="" >Shortly afterwards </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >a 14-year-old boy, </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >who cannot be named for legal reasons, began flying his model aeroplane on the same frequency after removing the blank peg from the board.
</New>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >Verdict</Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >: accidental death.
</New>


</body>
